The paper proposes a novel multiple template learning paradigm for structured prediction, which is a problem commonly studied in machine learning and natural language processing. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on two widely-studied structured prediction tasks, sequence labeling and dependency parsing, which are subfields of natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the proposed method involves feature extraction and processing, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS).
